Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the
@linguine{180%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

When boiling, add the linguine to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook
until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the saucepan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Stir-fry until browned all over, ~{6%minutes}.

Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and stir-fry until golden,
~{5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its
> packaging.

Add the garlic to the pan and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @creme fraiche{150%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and
@water{100%ml} for the sauce, stirring to combine.

Bring the sauce to a boil, then turn the heat down and simmer until thickened
slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook
> lardons thoroughly.

Stir the cooked pasta, @peas{120%g}, @butter{10%g} and half the
@Parmigiano Reggiano{20%g} into the sauce. Cook until the peas are piping hot,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's
a little too thick, then remove from the heat.

Share your ultimate creamy linguine alfredo between your bowls and sprinkle
over the remaining Parmigiano Reggiano.

Serve the @wild rocket{20%g} on the side with a drizzle of the
@balsamic glaze{12%g} to finish.

Enjoy!